### English Text Summary:
A video circulated on social media purportedly shows a missile from Yemen targeting a US aircraft carrier in the Red Sea, coinciding with rising tensions in the area and the Houthi group's announcement of missile and drone attacks against US forces. However, CNN Arabic verified the video and found it was actually filmed last year during the Russian-Ukrainian war, showing missiles flying over fishermen in the Caspian Sea. The video was originally posted on Instagram and later spread across various social media platforms. The Ukrainian military had reported that Russian missiles were attacking targets across Ukraine at low altitudes around the time the video was captured.

